p. The introduction and notes provide historical and literary contexts that make this ancient poetry more accessible to modern readers.Although this book is primarily aimed at the reader who does not know Greek, it would be a splendid supplement to a Greek language course. It will also have wide appeal for readers of' ancient literature, women's studies, mythology, and lovers of poetry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aFemmes et littératurexGrèce. 0aGreek poetryvTranslations into English. 0aGreek poetryxTranslations into EnglishxWomen authors. 0aGreek poetryxTranslations into English. 0aGreek poetryxWomen authorsvTranslations into English. 0aPoésie grecquexAnthologiesxTraductions anglaises. 0aWomen and literaturexGreece. 0aWomen and literaturezGreece. 0aÉcrits de femmes grecsxTraductions anglaises. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press eBook Package Archivez978311063534840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520910966423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520910966.jpg  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press eBook Package Archive  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles